title: Oshkosh finds footing
text:
(0) Comments 
A week after toppling top-ranked UW-Whitewater, UW-Oshkosh came out Saturday trying to avoid a major letdown. 
Thanks to two touchdown passes in the fourth quarter by Jayden Essman, Oshkosh was able to rally past UW-Stevens Point, 21-10, at home. 
The Pointers (3-3, 1-2 WIAC) struck first on a 36-yard pass from Matt Sosinky to Jared Pankow on the opening drive of the third, but the Titans (5-1, 3-0) answered on Dylan Hecker's 2-yard run. 
After Jesse Velvelde put Point back on top, 10-7, with a 31-yard field with 3:48 left in the third, Essman went to work. 
First he capped a 98-yard drive by Oshkosh with a 20-yard scoring strike to Zach Kasubowski on the first play of the fourth. 
Then on Oshkosh's next drive he connected with Sam Mentkowski on a 74-yard score. 
UW-Platteville 56, UW-River Falls 19: Tom Kelly had another big day for the Falcons (5-1, 2-1), but he shared the spotlight with Kyle Whitman in a throttling of the host Falcons (3-3, 2-1). 
Kelly threw for 314 yards and two touchdowns and added a score one the ground. Whitman carried only six times but found the end zone four times. 
UW-Stout 45, UW-Eau Claire 12: Brian Alvarez had 159 yards receiving and caught three of quarterback Hank Kujak's five touchdown passes for the visiting Blue Devils (2-4, 1-2) in victory over the rival Blugolds (0-6, 0-3). Â© 2015 , Journal Sentinel Inc. All rights reserved.
